1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
Have you ever gotten an urgent call
from a family member

2
00:00:03,000 --> 00:00:05,500
saying they're in trouble
and need money right away?

3
00:00:05,500 --> 00:00:09,000
Here's something scary: scammers can
now clone someone's voice

4
00:00:09,000 --> 00:00:12,500
using just a few seconds of audio
from social media.

5
00:00:12,500 --> 00:00:16,000
They call you pretending to be
your child or grandchild —

6
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:19,500
saying they're in an accident
or arrested and need money now.

7
00:00:19,500 --> 00:00:22,000
So what do you do?
The answer is simple:

8
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:25,000
hang up and call them back.

9
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:29,000
Call them on the number you already
have saved in your contacts —

10
00:00:29,000 --> 00:00:32,500
not the number that just called you.
Your real contact.

11
00:00:32,500 --> 00:00:36,500
You can also set up a family code word —
something only your family would know.

12
00:00:36,500 --> 00:00:40,500
Agree to use it in any emergency.
If they don't know it — hang up.

13
00:00:40,500 --> 00:00:44,000
The three red flags to remember:
extreme urgency,

14
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:47,000
requests for gift cards
or wire transfers,

15
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:50,500
and asking you to keep it secret
from other family members.

16
00:00:50,500 --> 00:00:55,000
Hang up, call them back on your
real number, set up a code word.

17
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:58,500
This one habit stops AI voice scams
every single time.

18
00:00:58,500 --> 00:01:02,500
For more free guides in plain English,
visit TekSure.com.

19
00:01:02,500 --> 00:01:05,000
[END]
